title: For Sale:  BRNO 8X57
postcontent: A Brno 8x57, mod. 22F.  This early model 22F LR Mauser and so marked Brno on the front ring and has all proff marks, was made  at the end of WW2 when the Nazi troops left The Cheq state In 1945. The Brno factory used a limited supply of Large ring actions that the German army left behind as they were forced to use the Brno plant to build military small arms...The commercial arms that followed were dubbed the 21 and 22F, the F meaning manlicher stocks  and the 21 being rifles..They quickly used up all the LR actions.  Then they used the round top G-33/40s they had on hand for the German Customs service mod 35 carbines,  later in 1950s Brno went to the double square bridge G33-40 (The latest mod. 21 and 22). using the same stock design as they did in the beginning, all of them used the same basic stock. This rifle is extremely rare and in excellent shape for a 117 year old rifle, has an excellent bore and and shoots great groups.  Has a historical background. The rifle is an awesome example of the old world the gun makers art, It has the beautiful ACORN bolt handle turned down for scope use, and drilled and taped by Jack Belk without disturbing the stamping on the front ring, has a single set trigger with a good trigger pull, 20 inch barrel with a full solid intregal rib with one standing rear sight, and front sight on a ramp all integral;  Original Mauser safety works with scope on the left side of the scope;  Old world rust blue is like new and always will be..Trigger guard has extension towards the grip cap, and has the oval glove trigger guard.  The front action ring is marked on top with CS.ST over  ZBROJOVKA  over BRNO, the scope holes do not interfere with the front ring inscriptions.
